I've read so many--
as I'm sure you have--

00:25:40.350 --> 00:25:43.850 align:middle line:84%
these death bed
regrets that people,

00:25:43.850 --> 00:25:46.390 align:middle line:84%
if I had my life
to do over again,

00:25:46.390 --> 00:25:49.300 align:middle line:84%
I would wear purple hats,
and I would do this,

00:25:49.300 --> 00:25:50.310 align:middle line:90%
and I would love this.

00:25:50.310 --> 00:25:54.240 align:middle line:84%
And I think that if you
have to wait till your dying

00:25:54.240 --> 00:25:56.130 align:middle line:84%
to make the types of
choices you should

00:25:56.130 --> 00:25:59.370 align:middle line:84%
make when you're
alive and vital,

00:25:59.370 --> 00:26:05.920 align:middle line:84%
then you don't know anything at
all about how powerful you are,

00:26:05.920 --> 00:26:08.790 align:middle line:84%
and what you should be
doing in this moment.

00:26:08.790 --> 00:26:12.250 align:middle line:84%
That in fact, the
choice to forgive,

00:26:12.250 --> 00:26:17.800 align:middle line:84%
the choice to love deeply,
the choice to empower others

00:26:17.800 --> 00:26:21.280 align:middle line:84%
are the choices you
should strive to make.

00:26:21.280 --> 00:26:25.660 align:middle line:84%
To become that kind of
soul inside of yourself.

00:26:25.660 --> 00:26:26.740 align:middle line:90%
